NAME
     size - Prints section sizes of common object files

SYNOPSIS
     size -doxV files

DESCRIPTION
   Purpose
     The size command produces section size information for each
     section in the common object files.  The size of the text,
     data, and bss (uninitialized data) sections are printed
     along with the total size of the object file.  If an archive
     file is input to the size command, the information for all
     archive members is displayed.

   Options
     -d   Prints numbers in decimal format, the default if -o or
          -x is not specified

     -o   Prints numbers in octal format instead of the default
          decimal format

     -x   Prints numbers in hexadecimal format instead of the
          default decimal format

     -V   Supplies version information on the size command

PROMPTS
   File name(s):
     Enter the name(s) of the object file(s) to be processed.

   Format (d,o,x):
     Enter d to display size in decimal format.  Enter o to
     display size in octal format.  Enter x to displays size in
     hexadecimal format.  The default is d.

   Print Version Number:
     Initial value is no. If you enter yes, the version number of
     the process is printed.

EXAMPLE
     The following command requests size information on the
     sections of an object file:

          size accept.o

     The result might be similar to the following:

          accept.o:  1440+24+0 = 1464b

